<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="30" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,1338,2010]" pageId="8" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,333,1555,1579]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="30" reason="1">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is a Latin adjective and refers to the half moon-shaped stripe of white scales present on the anterior border of the abdomen.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="30" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,1338,2010]" pageId="8" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1626,1651]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="30" reason="1">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Ruiz, 2011" authorityName="Ruiz" authorityYear="2011" box="[640,765,1627,1651]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Soesilarishius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="8" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinipes" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[640,765,1627,1651]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="30">S. spinipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[776,871,1627,1651]" pageId="8" pageNumber="30">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[776,871,1627,1651]" pageId="8" pageNumber="30" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
by having long spines on front legs, a reduced embolus in the male palp and four spermathecae in the epigyne, but can be distinguished from that species by the thinner embolus in the male palp (see 
<figureCitation box="[584,712,1698,1722]" captionStart="FIGURES 24–31" captionStartId="9.[151,263,1950,1973]" captionTargetBox="[171,1424,423,1928]" captionTargetId="figure-168@9.[151,1436,411,1940]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 24–31. Soesilarishius lunatus sp. nov. 24–25 left male palp (24 ventral, 25 retrolateral); 26 epigyne, ventral view; 27 vulva, dorsal view. Soesilarishius spinipes sp. nov. 28–29 left male palp (28 ventral, 29 retrolateral); 30 epigyne, ventral view; 31 vulva, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5280712" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5280712/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="30">Figs 24, 28</figureCitation>
) and by having a shorter duct connecting the secondary and the primary spermathecae in the epigyne (see 
<figureCitation box="[623,751,1734,1758]" captionStart="FIGURES 24–31" captionStartId="9.[151,263,1950,1973]" captionTargetBox="[171,1424,423,1928]" captionTargetId="figure-168@9.[151,1436,411,1940]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 24–31. Soesilarishius lunatus sp. nov. 24–25 left male palp (24 ventral, 25 retrolateral); 26 epigyne, ventral view; 27 vulva, dorsal view. Soesilarishius spinipes sp. nov. 28–29 left male palp (28 ventral, 29 retrolateral); 30 epigyne, ventral view; 31 vulva, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5280712" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5280712/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="30">Figs 27, 31</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[763,837,1734,1758]" captionStart="FIGURES 32–33" captionStartId="10.[151,263,1933,1956]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,1370,1913]" captionTargetId="figure-515@10.[151,1436,1354,1919]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 32–33. Soesilarishius lunatus sp. nov. 32 half of vulva, dorsal view. Soesilarishius spinipes sp. nov. 33 half of vulva, dorsal view. (cd) copulation duct; (co) copulation opening; (d) duct; (fd) fertilization duct; (ng) pores of nutritive glands; (ps) primary spermatheca; (sg) scent glands; (ss) secondary spermatheca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5280714" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5280714/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="30">32–33</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="32" pageId="8" pageNumber="30" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,1338,2010]" lastBlockId="9.[151,1436,151,356]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="31" pageId="8" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,533,1770,1795]" pageId="8" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis box="[199,344,1770,1795]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="30" reason="1">Description.</emphasis>
Male 
<typeStatus box="[421,528,1771,1795]" pageId="8" pageNumber="30">holotype</typeStatus>
:
</emphasis>
Total length: 2.75. Carapace dark brown, 1.50 long, 1.10 wide, 0.75 high, covered with sparse white scales (
<figureCitation box="[493,581,1806,1830]" captionStart="FIGURES 20–23" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,259,1889]" captionTargetId="figure-73@7.[151,1436,259,1895]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 20–23. Soesilarishius cymbialis sp. nov. 20 male habitus (paratype IBSP 160737); 21 female habitus (paratype IBSP 160728). Soesilarishius lunatus sp. nov. 22 male habitus (paratype IBSP 160756); 23 female habitus (paratype IBSP 160757)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5280710" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5280710/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="30">Figs 22</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[592,666,1806,1830]" captionStart="FIGURES 45–59" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1736,1759]" captionTargetBox="[286,1297,202,1703]" captionTargetId="figure-153@14.[271,1300,195,1716]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 45–59. Soesilarishius minimus sp. nov. 45–46 male carapace (45 dorsal, 46 lateral); Soesilarishius crispiventer sp. nov. 47–48 male carapace (47 dorsal, 48 lateral); Soesilarishius cymbialis sp. nov. 49–50 male carapace (49 dorsal, 50 lateral); Soesilarishius lunatus sp. nov. 51–52 male carapace (51 dorsal, 52 lateral); Soesilarishius spinipes sp. nov. 53–54 male carapace (53 dorsal, 54 lateral); Soesilarishius albipes sp. nov. 55–56 male carapace (55 dorsal, 56 lateral); Soesilarishius dromedarius sp. nov. 57–58 male carapace (57 dorsal, 58 lateral); Soesilarishius crispiventer sp. nov. 59 male abdomen, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5280720" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5280720/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="30">51–52</figureCitation>
). Ocular quadrangle 0.80 long. Anterior eye row 1.12 wide and posterior 0.97 wide. Chelicera dark brown. Labium and sternum dark brown. Endite dark brown, slightly projected laterally. Palp dark brown, with a short RTA, tegulum projected proximally and with a distal bump, and short, distal embolus (
<figureCitation box="[260,392,1914,1938]" captionStart="FIGURES 24–31" captionStartId="9.[151,263,1950,1973]" captionTargetBox="[171,1424,423,1928]" captionTargetId="figure-168@9.[151,1436,411,1940]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 24–31. Soesilarishius lunatus sp. nov. 24–25 left male palp (24 ventral, 25 retrolateral); 26 epigyne, ventral view; 27 vulva, dorsal view. Soesilarishius spinipes sp. nov. 28–29 left male palp (28 ventral, 29 retrolateral); 30 epigyne, ventral view; 31 vulva, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5280712" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5280712/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="30">Figs 24–25</figureCitation>
). Legs 4312; I dark brown with yellow tarsus; II dark brown, with light brown metatarsus and yellow tarsus; III and IV dark brown with yellow metatarsi and tarsi, and groups of white scales on distal, dorsal portion of tibiae. Length of femur: I 0.92, II 0.75, III 0.95, IV 0.87; patella + tibia: I 1.10, II 0.82, III 1.00, IV 0.95; metatarsus + tarsus: I 0.77, II 0.75, III 1.00, IV 1.15. Spination: femur I d1-1-1, II-III d1-1-1, p0-0-1, IV d1-1-1; patella I p1, II 0, III–IV r1; tibia I v2-2-2 (for proportion, see 
