<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,151,896]" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,593,151,176]" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">
Female (
<typeStatus box="[302,411,151,176]" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">paratype</typeStatus>
IBSP 160620):
</emphasis>
Total length: 3.25. Carapace dark brown, 1.62 long, 1.20 wide, 0.80 high (
<figureCitation box="[159,242,188,212]" captionStart="FIGURES 20–23" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,259,1889]" captionTargetId="figure-73@7.[151,1436,259,1895]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 20–23. Soesilarishius cymbialis sp. nov. 20 male habitus (paratype IBSP 160737); 21 female habitus (paratype IBSP 160728). Soesilarishius lunatus sp. nov. 22 male habitus (paratype IBSP 160756); 23 female habitus (paratype IBSP 160757)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5280710" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5280710/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
). Ocular quadrangle 0.97 long. Anterior eye row 1.25 wide and posterior 1.10 wide. Chelicera light brown. Labium, sternum and endite light brown. Palp yellow. Legs 4312; I light brown, fading towards tarsus; II yellow; III with dark brown femur, light brown patella, yellow tibia with the proximal portion dark brown and a dark brown small area on the prolateral, distal portion; metatarsus and tarsus yellow; IV with dark brown femur, yellow patella with a dark brown distal portion, tibia as in III, yellow metatarsus with a dark brown proximal area and yellow tarsus. Length of femur: I 1.00, II 0.80, III 0.97, IV 0.95; patella + tibia: I 1.25, II 0.90, III 1.07, IV 1.10; metatarsus + tarsus: I 0.80, II 0.80, III 1.07, IV 1.30. Spination: femur I–II d1-1-1, III d1-1-1, p1di, IV d1-1-1, r1di; patella I p1, II 0, III p1, r1, IV r1; tibia I v2-2-2 (for proportion, see 
<figureCitation box="[766,847,439,463]" captionStart="FIGURES 60–65" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1781,1804]" captionTargetBox="[166,1421,636,1742]" captionTargetId="figure-245@15.[151,1436,628,1758]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 60–65. Soesilarishius lunatus sp. nov. 60 male leg I, prolateral view, showing ventral spines; 61 female leg I, prolateral view, showing ventral spines; Soesilarishius albipes sp. nov. 62 male leg I, prolateral view, showing ventral spines; 63 female leg I, prolateral view, showing ventral spines; Soesilarishius crispiventer sp. nov. 64 male leg I, prolateral view, showing ventral spines; 65 female leg I, prolateral view, showing ventral spines." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5280722" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5280722/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">Fig. 61</figureCitation>
), II v2-2-2, p0-1, III v1p-0, p1-1, r1-1, IV v1p-0, p1- 1, r1-1; metatarsus I v2-2, II v2-2, p1-1, III v2-2, p1-2, r1-2, IV v2di, p1-2, r1-1-2. Abdomen as in male, except for the posterior markings, less conspicuous (
<figureCitation box="[629,714,511,535]" captionStart="FIGURES 20–23" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,259,1889]" captionTargetId="figure-73@7.[151,1436,259,1895]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 20–23. Soesilarishius cymbialis sp. nov. 20 male habitus (paratype IBSP 160737); 21 female habitus (paratype IBSP 160728). Soesilarishius lunatus sp. nov. 22 male habitus (paratype IBSP 160756); 23 female habitus (paratype IBSP 160757)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5280710" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5280710/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
). Epigyne with anterior, semicircular copulation opening (for a better understanding of this complex epigyne, epigynal structures mentioned here refer to only one of the sides); a short copulation duct leads to a globose secondary spermatheca, in which scent glands open; this secondary spermatheca is connected to the primary spermatheca by a short duct; pores of nutritive glands are present on the wall of the primary spermatheca, beside which the fertilization duct arises (
<figureCitation box="[938,1068,655,679]" captionStart="FIGURES 24–31" captionStartId="9.[151,263,1950,1973]" captionTargetBox="[171,1424,423,1928]" captionTargetId="figure-168@9.[151,1436,411,1940]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 24–31. Soesilarishius lunatus sp. nov. 24–25 left male palp (24 ventral, 25 retrolateral); 26 epigyne, ventral view; 27 vulva, dorsal view. Soesilarishius spinipes sp. nov. 28–29 left male palp (28 ventral, 29 retrolateral); 30 epigyne, ventral view; 31 vulva, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5280712" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5280712/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">Figs 26–27</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1079,1111,655,679]" captionStart="FIGURES 32–33" captionStartId="10.[151,263,1933,1956]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,1370,1913]" captionTargetId="figure-515@10.[151,1436,1354,1919]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 32–33. Soesilarishius lunatus sp. nov. 32 half of vulva, dorsal view. Soesilarishius spinipes sp. nov. 33 half of vulva, dorsal view. (cd) copulation duct; (co) copulation opening; (d) duct; (fd) fertilization duct; (ng) pores of nutritive glands; (ps) primary spermatheca; (sg) scent glands; (ss) secondary spermatheca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5280714" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5280714/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="32">32</figureCitation>
). Spinnerets dark brown.
</paragraph>
